 102:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     [..]
 103:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     Use function HAL_UART_UnRegisterCallback() to reset a callback to the default
 104:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     weak (surcharged) function.
 105:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     HAL_UART_UnRegisterCallback() takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle,
 106:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     and the Callback ID.
 107:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     This function allows to reset following callbacks:
 108:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) TxHalfCpltCallback        : Tx Half Complete Callback.
 109:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) TxCpltCallback            : Tx Complete Callback.
 110:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) RxHalfCpltCallback        : Rx Half Complete Callback.
 111:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) RxCpltCallback            : Rx Complete Callback.
 112:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) ErrorCallback             : Error Callback.
 113:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) AbortCpltCallback         : Abort Complete Callback.
 114:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) AbortTransmitCpltCallback : Abort Transmit Complete Callback.
 115:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) AbortReceiveCpltCallback  : Abort Receive Complete Callback.
 116:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) MspInitCallback           : UART MspInit.
 117:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     (+) MspDeInitCallback         : UART MspDeInit.
 118:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c **** 
 119:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     [..]
 120:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     For specific callback RxEventCallback, use dedicated registration/reset functions:
 121:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     respectively HAL_UART_RegisterRxEventCallback() , HAL_UART_UnRegisterRxEventCallback().
 122:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c **** 
 123:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     [..]
 124:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     By default, after the HAL_UART_Init() and when the state is HAL_UART_STATE_RESET
 125:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     all callbacks are set to the corresponding weak (surcharged) functions:
 126:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     examples HAL_UART_TxCpltCallback(), HAL_UART_RxHalfCpltCallback().
 127:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit functions that are respectively
 128:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     reset to the legacy weak (surcharged) functions in the HAL_UART_Init()
 129:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     and HAL_UART_DeInit() only when these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
 130:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     If not, MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the HAL_UART_Init() and HAL_UART_DeInit()
 131:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand).
 132:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c **** 
 133:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     [..]
 134:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in HAL_UART_STATE_READY state only.
 135:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     Exception done MspInit/MspDeInit that can be registered/unregistered
 136:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     in HAL_UART_STATE_READY or HAL_UART_STATE_RESET state, thus registered (user)
 137:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used during the Init/DeInit.
 138:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     In that case first register the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 139:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     using HAL_UART_RegisterCallback() before calling HAL_UART_DeInit()
 140:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     or HAL_UART_Init() function.
 141:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c **** 
 142:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     [..]
 143:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     When The compilation define USE_HAL_UART_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 144:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     not defined, the callback registration feature is not available
 145:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     and weak (surcharged) callbacks are used.
