 188:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     [..] This subsection also provides a set of additional functions providing enhanced reception
 189:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     services to user. (For example, these functions allow application to handle use cases
 190:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     where number of data to be received is unknown).
 191:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c **** 
 192:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     (#) Compared to standard reception services which only consider number of received
 193:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****         data elements as reception completion criteria, these functions also consider additional ev
 194:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****         as triggers for updating reception status to caller :
 195:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****        (+) Detection of inactivity period (RX line has not been active for a given period).
 196:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****           (++) RX inactivity detected by IDLE event, i.e. RX line has been in idle state (normally 
 197:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****                for 1 frame time, after last received byte.
 198:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c **** 
 199:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****     (#) There are two mode of transfer:
 200:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****        (+) Blocking mode: The reception is performed in polling mode, until either expected number 
 201:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****            or till IDLE event occurs. Reception is handled only during function execution.
 202:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****            When function exits, no data reception could occur. HAL status and number of actually re
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccQKxCKQ.s 			page 5


 203:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****            are returned by function after finishing transfer.
 204:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****        (+) Non-Blocking mode: The reception is performed using Interrupts or DMA.
 205:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****            These API's return the HAL status.
 206:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****            The end of the data processing will be indicated through the
 207:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****            dedicated UART IRQ when using Interrupt mode or the DMA IRQ when using DMA mode.
 208:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****            The HAL_UARTEx_RxEventCallback() user callback will be executed during Receive process
 209:./STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_uart.c ****            The HAL_UART_ErrorCallback()user callback will be executed when a reception error is det
